CRITICAL WARNING & PROHIBITION
厳重警告および禁止事項

[English Version]

Any form of utilizing this project's achievements (including but not limited to its source code, architectural logic, user interface designs, and page screenshots) to feed into Artificial Intelligence (AI), Large Language Models (LLMs), or any other automated tools for reading, analysis, or the generation of similar functional or visual outcomes is strictly prohibited by the developers.
We issue this strict warning against "plagiarism" and "code laundering" under the guise of AI. While we deeply respect the open-source spirit, we absolutely do not tolerate the unjust exploitation of our labor disguised as AI generation.

HOW TO OBTAIN AUTHORIZATION (INCLUDING COMMERCIAL USE)
We are not rejecting technological development or collaboration. If you wish to use or reference the achievements of this project, please contact us in advance to obtain explicit authorization.
If proper communication is established, we will gladly grant permission in most cases, even for commercial projects. We welcome approaches that follow the proper channels.

RETROACTIVE AUTHORIZATION & AMNESTY CLAUSE
If you have already utilized the achievements of this project prior to the publication of this notice (including but not limited to feeding source code, architectural logic, or page screenshots into AI for reading, analysis, or replication), we strongly recommend that you contact us immediately to apply for retroactive authorization.
Evidence Preservation: Regarding suspected cases of plagiarism or replication of this project's achievements currently in the market, we have already completed the preservation (screening and recording) of all relevant evidence.

LEGAL ACTION
If unauthorized plagiarism, imitation, or AI-assisted reproduction is discovered without explicit written consent or the completion of retroactive authorization procedures, we will resolutely take all legal measures, including filing lawsuits, seeking injunctions, and claiming damages, to protect our legitimate rights.

Please respect the open-source spirit. Respect for creators is the foundation of a healthy developer community.


